# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 🛡️ SCAMESCAPE ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES - Setup Guide
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env in the project root and fill in your actual values

# ─── Application Configuration ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
ENVIRONMENT=production
DEBUG=false
FRONTEND_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000

# ─── GROQ API Key (PRIMARY - REQUIRED) ───────────────────────────────────────────
# Free tier available - get key from: https://console.groq.com/keys
# Model: llama-3.3-70b-versatile
# ✅ Working perfectly with no rate limits
GROQ_API_KEY=gsk_your_groq_api_key_here
GROQ_BASE_URL=https://api.groq.com/openai/v1

# ─── OpenAI API Key (OPTIONAL - Not currently needed) ─────────────────────────────
# Get from: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# Status: Over quota (insufficient_quota error)
# OPENAI_API_KEY=sk_test_your_openai_key_here

# ─── OpenRouter API Key (OPTIONAL - Not currently needed) ──────────────────────────
# Get from: https://openrouter.ai/keys  
# Status: Configuration error (HTTP 405)
# OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk_or_your_openrouter_key_here

# ─── Database Configuration ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MongoDB URL - choose one:
# Local: mongodb://localhost:27017
# Atlas: mongodb+srv://username:password@cluster.mongodb.net/?retryWrites=true&w=majority
MONGODB_URL=mongodb://localhost:27017
DATABASE_NAME=scamescape

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 📋 QUICK START - SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1️⃣  GET GROQ API KEY (FREE, NO CREDIT CARD):
#
#     Visit: https://console.groq.com/keys
#     a) Sign up with email
#     b) Create new API key (starts with "gsk_")
#     c) Copy and paste into GROQ_API_KEY above
#     d) Save this file as .env in project root
#
#     ✅ No rate limits on free tier
#     ✅ Supports llama-3.3-70b model
#     ✅ Chat & call generation use GROQ exclusively

# 2️⃣  SETUP MONGODB (Choose one option):
#
#     OPTION A - Local MongoDB (Development):
#     - Download: https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community
#     - Install on your machine
#     - Start MongoDB service
#     - Keep default: MONGODB_URL=mongodb://localhost:27017
#
#     OPTION B - MongoDB Atlas (Cloud, FREE tier available):
#     - Visit: https://www.mongodb.com/cloud/atlas
#     - Create free account
#     - Create free cluster
#     - Click "Connect" → "Drivers"
#     - Copy your connection string (includes username:password)
#     - Update MONGODB_URL with your connection string
#
# 3️⃣  VERIFY SETUP:
#
#     Backend (Python):
#     $ cd backend
#     $ python -m uvicorn app.main:app --reload
#     Look for: ✅ GROQ AI Client initialized successfully
#
#     Frontend (Next.js):
#     $ cd frontend  
#     $ npm run dev
#     Open: http://localhost:3000
#
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 📝 Notes:
# - Keep .env secure - never commit to version control
# - .env.example shows structure but has dummy values
# - Use actual API keys in your .env file (git-ignored)
# - Environment variables are loaded by backend on startup

